         <abstract>
            <p>We give a deterministic algorithm for finding all primitive representations of a natural number $n$ in the form $fu^2 + gv^2$, where $f$ and $g$ are given positive coprime integers, and $n \geq f + g + 1, (n, fg) = 1$. The running time of this algorithm is at most $$\mathscr{O}(n^{1/4}(\log n)^3(\log \log n)(\log \log \log n)),$$ uniformly in $f$ and $g$.</p>
          </abstract>
